Anthony Fantan oh here Internet's
busiest music nerd this is an album
review for the new wolf parade LP Expo
86 before I get into this review I want
to tell y'all that there is a new track
from the band these are powers up at the
needle drop calm right now it's good
times find a link to download it in the
d box wolf parade is a Canadian rock
quartet that has masterminded for the
most part by two different songwriters
Dan Buettner and Spencer crew and these
two guys are unbelievably busy a lot of
side projects and I've been known to
enjoy myself some sunset rub down some
frog eyes some handsome furs and some
Swan Lake - what I love about these guys
is that no matter what song they're
singing dan and Spencer just let
everything just pour out all over to the
track just spilling everything
everywhere emotions all over the place
can't control the mood and how Dan and
Spencer stay together in a band is
completely beyond me it's a tribute to
working together because to me they are
very very different songwriters of
course Dan is way more visceral way more
of a hook man and all about being
straightforward and to the point Spencer
on the other hand is much more into
unconventional things abstract lyrics
very weird song structures stopping
building instrumentation back up and
starting again he has a much stronger
experimental side but these differences
on Expo 86 have for the most part
disappeared this album really shoots for
a consistent sound using production to
maintain a cohesive aesthetic you could
just land on any track on this album and
you're bound to find some really booming
loud drums a lot of burning guitar
distortion and some extremely bright
reverb on the vocals it's really a rock
record and the most
no nonsense that wolf parade has ever
been I mean if these guys have ever
dawdled a little bit too much for your
taste this may be the time to give them
second chance but I am turned off quite
a bit by the production the reverb is so
freaking loud on the vocals that it's
almost distracting and it really doesn't
complement dan's vocals or Spencer
because something that both of them have
in common is that they like to do a lot
of vocal yelping and of course this
yelping is only magnified by the fact
that you're hearing it repeated two or
three times by the echo also this album
is really really compressed just
everything is so thick and loud and
voluminous throughout every track from
beginning to end
even the points at which there is less
instrumentation it is loud which really
kills the dynamics of these songs but I
get it the band is clearly going for
some kind of gut reaction get loud don't
think just rock however this sue to me
fits Beckner much more snugly than it
does Krug Dan is as energetic as he's
ever been writing songs that go from
zero to 60 in a second flat while
Spencer's usual experiments with volume
and swells stopping and starting are
kind of silenced on this album not only
by the production which I do not think
complements him but by trying to write
songs like Dan in a catchy or fashion
but I wouldn't say Spencer's attempts at
this are completely fruitless what would
my lovers say is one of my favorite
tracks on this and chaos Appian is one
of the most fiery songs on this album
this record most definitely grooves it
moves there's a lot of tight tight
playing on this thing it's a beat cracks
like thunder picks a sound and sticks to
its guns it's most definitely an
admirable release but sometimes this
direction worked for me and other times
it didn't in fact quite a few times it
didn't I'm feeling a strong 6 - a light
7 on this just about in that area I
thought it was okay I didn't really hate
this album but let me know what you
